File: Janusz Walus is serving a life sentence for gunning down SA Communist Party leader Hani in 1993. JOHANNESBURG - Judgement has been reserved in the parole matter of Chris Hani's assassin. Janusz Walus is challenging the decision not to grant him parole earlier this year.  The legal team of former Justice minister, Michael Masutha, has argued that the denial of parole was well reasoned. Walus is serving a life sentence for gunning down SA Communist Party leader Hani in 1993.